And that's a completely
legitimate way, and hopefully

00:05:59.180 --> 00:06:01.550
it will make some connections
between what slope is.

00:06:01.550 --> 00:06:05.670
So what is the change in blocks
for a change in x.

00:06:05.670 --> 00:06:11.050
So when we went from x going
from 1 to 2-- so our change in

00:06:11.050 --> 00:06:15.350
x here would be 2 minus 1, we
increased by 1 --what was our

00:06:15.350 --> 00:06:16.700
change in blocks?

00:06:16.700 --> 00:06:19.580
It would be 4, or 5 minus 1.

00:06:19.580 --> 00:06:21.740
It's 5 minus 1.

00:06:21.740 --> 00:06:22.560
And what is this equal to?

00:06:22.560 --> 00:06:28.330
This is equal to 4 over 1,
which is equal to 4.

00:06:28.330 --> 00:06:29.710
Let me scroll over
a little bit.

00:06:29.710 --> 00:06:34.380
So our change in blocks, or
change in x is 4, or our slope

00:06:34.380 --> 00:06:35.890
is equal to 4.

00:06:35.890 --> 00:06:39.920
So if you want to do this kind
of the setting up the equation

00:06:39.920 --> 00:06:42.900
of a line way, you would say
that our equation-- If, well

00:06:42.900 --> 00:06:43.460
let me write it.

00:06:43.460 --> 00:06:54.130
Number of blocks are going to
be equal to 4 times the term

00:06:54.130 --> 00:06:56.970
that we're dealing with,
the term in our

00:06:56.970 --> 00:07:00.490
pattern, plus some constant.

00:07:00.490 --> 00:07:02.260
This right here is the
equation of a line.

00:07:02.260 --> 00:07:05.135
If it's completely foreign to
you, just do it the way we did

00:07:05.135 --> 00:07:07.330
it earlier in the video.

00:07:07.330 --> 00:07:10.370
And so, how do we solve
for this constant?

00:07:10.370 --> 00:07:12.320
Well, we use one of
our terms here.

00:07:12.320 --> 00:07:14.960
We know that when we had one--
In our first term we

00:07:14.960 --> 00:07:16.700
only had one block.

00:07:16.700 --> 00:07:17.750
So let's put that here.

00:07:17.750 --> 00:07:22.760
So in our first term-- we're
going to have that b right

00:07:22.760 --> 00:07:25.390
there --we only had one block.

00:07:25.390 --> 00:07:28.830
So we have 1 is equal
to 4 plus b.

00:07:28.830 --> 00:07:33.260
If you subtract 4 from both
sides of this equation, so you

00:07:33.260 --> 00:07:36.240
subtract 4 from both sides,
what do you get?

00:07:36.240 --> 00:07:40.360
On the left-hand side, 1 minus
4 is negative 3, and that's

00:07:40.360 --> 00:07:43.260
equal to-- these 4's cancel
out --and and

00:07:43.260 --> 00:07:45.030
that's equal to b.

00:07:45.030 --> 00:07:46.970
So another way to get the
equation of a line, we have

00:07:46.970 --> 00:07:49.910
just solved that b is
equal to negative 3.

00:07:49.910 --> 00:07:53.960
We said how much do the number
of blocks change for a certain

00:07:53.960 --> 00:07:56.660
change in x, which is a change
in the number blocks for a

00:07:56.660 --> 00:07:58.680
change in x, we saw
it's always 4.

00:07:58.680 --> 00:08:00.230
4 per change in x.

00:08:00.230 --> 00:08:03.510
When x changes by 1,
we change by 4.

00:08:03.510 --> 00:08:05.630
That gave us our slope.

00:08:05.630 --> 00:08:08.535
And then to solve for-- If you
view this as a line, although

00:08:08.535 --> 00:08:12.120
this is only defined
on integers, I

00:08:12.120 --> 00:08:14.550
guess positive integers.

00:08:14.550 --> 00:08:17.230
In this situation, you could
view this as a y-intercept.

